\textbf{Conclusions}

In this work a new fractional-order operator without singular kernel, which
is an analog of the Riemann-Liouville fractional derivative with singular
kernel, was proposed for the first time. An illustrative example for
modelling the fractional-order steady heat flow was given and the analytical
solution for the governing~equation~involving the fractional derivative
without singular kernel was discussed.

